# Sample Pet Store API

This is a sample API for managing pets in a pet store.

HOST: https://petstore.example.com

# Group Pets

Resources related to pets in the pet store.

## Pets Collection [/pets]

### List All Pets [GET /pets]

Retrieve a list of all pets.

+ Parameters
    + limit (number, optional) - Maximum number of results to return
        + Default: 20
    + status (string, optional) - Filter by pet status
        + Members
            + `available`
            + `pending`
            + `sold`

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            [
                {
                    "id": 1,
                    "name": "Fluffy",
                    "type": "cat",
                    "status": "available"
                },
                {
                    "id": 2,
                    "name": "Rex",
                    "type": "dog",
                    "status": "sold"
                }
            ]

### Create a New Pet [POST /pets]

Create a new pet in the store.

+ Request (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "name": "Buddy",
                "type": "dog",
                "age": 3
            }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /pets/3

    + Body

            {
                "id": 3,
                "name": "Buddy",
                "type": "dog",
                "age": 3,
                "status": "available"
            }

+ Response 400 (application/json)

    Invalid input data

    + Body

            {
                "error": "Invalid pet data",
                "message": "Name is required"
            }

## Pet [/pets/{id}]

A single Pet object with all its details.

+ Parameters
    + id: 1 (number, required) - The unique ID of the pet

### Get a Pet [GET]

Retrieve a single pet by ID.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "id": 1,
                "name": "Fluffy",
                "type": "cat",
                "age": 2,
                "status": "available",
                "created_at": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"
            }

+ Response 404 (application/json)

    Pet not found

    + Body

            {
                "error": "Not Found",
                "message": "Pet with ID 1 not found"
            }

### Update a Pet [PUT]

Update an existing pet.

+ Request (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "name": "Fluffy Jr.",
                "age": 3
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "id": 1,
                "name": "Fluffy Jr.",
                "type": "cat",
                "age": 3,
                "status": "available"
            }

+ Response 404 (application/json)

    Pet not found

### Delete a Pet [DELETE]

Remove a pet from the store.

+ Response 204

+ Response 404 (application/json)

    Pet not found

# Group Users

User management operations.

## Users Collection [/users]

### List Users [GET /users]

Get a list of all users.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            [
                {
                    "id": 1,
                    "name": "John Doe",
                    "email": "john@example.com"
                },
                {
                    "id": 2,
                    "name": "Jane Smith",
                    "email": "jane@example.com"
                }
            ]

### Create User [POST /users]

Register a new user.

+ Request (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "name": "Bob Wilson",
                "email": "bob@example.com",
                "password": "securepassword123"
            }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "id": 3,
                "name": "Bob Wilson",
                "email": "bob@example.com",
                "created_at": "2024-01-20T08:00:00Z"
            }

+ Response 409 (application/json)

    Email already exists

    + Body

            {
                "error": "Conflict",
                "message": "Email already registered"
            }

## User [/users/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id (number, required) - User ID

### Get User [GET]

Get user details.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "id": 1,
                "name": "John Doe",
                "email": "john@example.com",
                "role": "customer"
            }

+ Response 404

    User not found
